Three on-ramps to running code.

Pick by what you are doing. The read eval print loop, with i-python, for one-line checks. A script, for a one-file utility — python my-script dot p-y. Optionally make it executable with a hash-bang slash u-s-r slash bin slash env python three on the first line. A project, for anything with multiple files, dependencies, tests, or that you will publish or deploy. Has a py-project dot t-o-m-l, a dot venv, a tests directory, often a source layout.
